{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778900864189,"sessionID":"ses_1d1506425ffepDMdDIQ77JhLYz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-80ecd5dca48534b9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Research for Ferritinophagy (Ferritin-specific autophagy)\n\n## PMID:38714719 \"Structural basis for the intracellular regulation of ferritin degradation.\"\nThis paper discusses the structural basis for how ferritin degradation is regulated intracellularly.\n- SUPPORT: PMID:38714719 \"Structural basis for the intracellular regulation of ferritin degradation.\"\n    - Discusses the regulation of ferritin degradation.\n\n## PMID:25327288 \"Selective VPS34 inhibitor blocks autophagy and uncovers a role for NCOA4 in ferritin degradation and iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\nThis paper identifies the role of NCOA4 in the selective autophagy of ferritin to maintain iron homeostasis.\n- SUPPORT: PMID:25327288 \"Selective VPS34 inhibitor blocks autophagy and uncovers a role for NCOA4 in ferritin degradation and iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\n    - identifies NCOA4 as a cargo receptor for ferritinophagy.\n\n## PMID:26436293 \"Ferritinophagy via NCOA4 is required for erythropoiesis and is regulated by iron dependent HERC2-mediated proteolysis.\"\nThis paper discusses ferritinophagy mediated by NCOA4 and its role in erythropoiesis.\n- SUPPORT: PMID:26436293 \"Ferritinophagy via NCOA4 is required for erythropoiesis and is regulated by iron dependent HERC2-mediated proteolysis.\"\n    - Confirms the term 'ferritinophagy' and the involvement of NCOA4.\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1778900864181,"end":1778900864188}},"id":"prt_e2ebf5f6c001K16oRb6Kj7q6rb","sessionID":"ses_1d1506425ffepDMdDIQ77JhLYz","messag